onferred to moths by bat-detecting ears. Moth tails lured bat attacks to these wing regions during 55% of interactions between bats and intact luna moths. We analyzed flight kinematics of moths with and without hindwing tails and suggest that tails have a minimal role in flight performance. Using a robust phylogeny, we find that long spatulate tails have independently evolved four times in saturniid moths, further supporting the selective advantage of this anti-bat strategy. Diversionary tactics are perhaps more common than appreciated in predator\u2013prey interactions. Our finding suggests that focusing on the sensory ecologies of key predators will reveal such countermeasures in prey.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Barber, Jesse R.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Leavell, Brian C.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Keener, Adam L.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Breinholt, Jesse W.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Chadwell, Brad A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "McClure, Christopher J. W.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hill, Geena M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kawahara, Akito Y.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/360c1adaefc49c8bf31ef81ad46fbae0", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/d250d5ae59f62b540d1a8e41f03341371a69d7bcd0ccc80cc275e51dbaf2c654", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/CTWP5YY2", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/CTWP5YY2", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/c5627dd3844570f3bb12ba3c66c06e6e!/b312365-314920", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": 